<subSubSection lastPageNumber="606" pageNumber="605" type="discussion">
<paragraph lastPageNumber="606" pageNumber="605">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="605">Note:</emphasis>
The Rumphius plate upon which this name was apparently based is cited in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1753)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Justicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpurea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="605">Justicia purpurea</emphasis>
L. (1753)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeus’">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
later accounts of that species (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="606">Syst. Nat.</emphasis>
, ed. 10, 2: 850. 1759; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="606">Sp. Pl.</emphasis>
, ed. 2, 1: 23. 1762), suggesting strongly that 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Jussiaea”">&quot;Jussiaea&quot;</normalizedToken>
was an error for 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Justicia”">&quot;Justicia&quot;</normalizedToken>
, as noted by Merrill (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="606">Interpret. Rumph. Herb. Amb.</emphasis>
: 476. 1917). &quot;
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1753" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1754" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Jussiaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpurea">Jussiaea purpurea</taxonomicName>
&quot; was not used by Linnaeus again in 1759 or 1762. It is treated as an orthographic variant of 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Justicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpurea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="606">Justicia purpurea</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
